      "span_text": "However, as illustrated in Figure 2a , there is now widespread agreement that longitudinally oriented actin cables run along the length of tip-growing cells, and that a dense meshwork of fine actin filaments occupies an area near the tip but does not extend to the extreme apex (e.g., Miller et al. 1996 , Kost et al. 1998 , Miller et al. 1999 , Ketelaar et al. 2002 [CITATION_1] , although highly dynamic actin filaments have been reported to penetrate transiently into the apex (Fu et al. 2001 ).",
